SITUATION: 28-year-old G3P2 with established rh incompatibility attending for routine follow-up

BACKGROUND: Diagnosed with rh incompatibility at 12 weeks gestation. Currently 38+6 weeks. Previous pregnancies complicated by similar issues. BMI 28. Non-smoker. Partner supportive. Lives locally with good social support.

ASSESSMENT: Patient reports good compliance with treatment regimen. Symptoms well controlled on current management. Observations stable: BP 130/80, HR 76, afebrile. Urine dipstick...
